translated: Kihlström, Olof Emanuel, editor, Mariestad, b. 8/6/93 in Österfärnebo, Gävleb. 1st, son of Erik K. and Anna Ek. Married to Alva Hallin. Children: Astrid b. 1922, Ulla b. 1936, Anna-Britt b. 1939. — Sithlm-s private high school 1918. Studied Norwegian press in 1932. Collaborator in Värmlands Länstidning from 1916, Norrtälje Tidning from 1918-1921, Bärgslagsposten from 1922-1926, editor for Ludvika-Posten from 1926-1927, collaborator in Jönköpings Läns Tidning from 1927-1935, member of the folk party from 1935-1936, owner and editor of Mariestads Länstidning since 1936, editor of Kvarntidningen since 1943. Secretary of the Skaraborg 1st constituency association since 1937, member of the SBU board from 1937-1947, vice chairman of the Skaraborg 1st Blue Ribbon Association since 1940, member of the town council since 1942 and the finance committee since the same year, chairman of the Mariestad Blue Ribbon Association since 1940. Hobby: cycling.
